Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State has urged traditional rulers in the state to maintain peace in their communities.
Gov Sule made the call at the palace of the Esu Karu, Chief Luka Panya-Baba, as part of activities commemorating his second year in office and to get feedback from the people.
The governor said, as custodians of the culture and tradition of the people, traditional rulers must be seen as a rallying point for the maintenance of communal peace and social development.